Package com.rb.biz.types

Class SignedMoney

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Number
com.rb.nonbiz.types.RBNumeric<T>
com.rb.nonbiz.types.PreciseValue<SignedMoney>
com.rb.biz.types.SignedMoney
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SignedMoney>
public class SignedMoney
extends PreciseValue<SignedMoney>
A typesafe representation of money that also allows for negative values.

The plain Money class only allows >= 0 values, so you'll need this for those rare cases where you want to represent a negative amount.

See Also:
Money, Serialized Form
